    Pro will change the protection flags and comment of any file
    
    Pro will ONLY run on AmigaDos 2.04

Note:

    Use Pro at your own risk.

Starting:

    »» Workbench ««

        Click on Pro, press shift and click on files to change,
        double click on the last file to start Pro.

        Click on Pro twice.

    »» Cli ««

        Pro

Usage:

        Gadgets -

            Name        - File name

            Comment     - File comment, If editing the comment make sure
                          you press return at the end, or the string will
                          not be copied to the file when saved.

            Hidden      - Not used.

            Script      - The text file will be executed when called from
                          the shell.

            Pure        - The file is a pure command and can be made resident.

            Archived    - The file has been archived

            Readable    - The file can be read.

            Writable    - The file can be written to (altered).

            Executable  - The file is executable (a program).

            Deletable   - The file can be deleted.

            Next        - Only Enabled when there is more than one file
                          Selected from Workbench before starting Pro.
                          Show next file.


            Prev        - Only Enabled when there is more than one file
                          Selected from Workbench before starting Pro.
                          Show previous file.

            Load        - Load file, brings up Asl file requester.
                          Replaces file or files in memory.
                          Disables Prev and Next Gadgets.

            Save        - Save's file.

            Quit        - Quit program.

